</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="496" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,439,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[321,431,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuata">
<emphasis box="[321,431,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">S. sinuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[555,719,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mishmiensis">
<emphasis box="[555,719,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">S. mishmiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[772,862,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi">
<emphasis box="[772,862,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">S. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the crown and in having the arms of the ventral process of the aedeagus setose dorsally and crossing over each other at the base. However, it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[212,301,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi">
<emphasis box="[212,301,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">S. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the ventral process of the pygofer exceeding the dorsal margin of the pygofer lobe and from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,316,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mishmiensis">
<emphasis box="[151,316,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">S. mishmiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having two pairs of atrial processes (one pair in 
<taxonomicName box="[890,1055,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mishmiensis">
<emphasis box="[890,1055,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="496">S. mishmiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
